                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>MR. ABRAHAM VAN OVER. I live at Nine Elms, Batter-sea. On the 31st of October, between three and four o'clock, I was standing on 'Change, talking to some gentlemen near the centre - my handkerchief was safe a few minutes before. I did not see the prisoner until a gentleman tapped me on the shoulder - he had hold of the prisoner's hand with the handkerchief in it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-68-person590">
                  LIPMAN 
                  WOOLF DRACH
               <interp inst="t18221204-68-person590" type="surname" value="WOOLF DRACH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-68-person590" type="given" value="LIPMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-68-person590" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , I live in Castle-street, St. Mary Axe. I was on 'Change, and saw the prisoner put his hand into Mr. Van Over's pocket and take the handkerchief out. I laid hold of his hand with it in it, and told the prosecutor. We took him to the Mansion-house.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ANDREWS. Q. There was a crowd there - A. Yes, it was a busy day. I was close to him and am sure he took it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221204-68-person591">
                  DANIEL 
                  FORRESTER
               <interp inst="t18221204-68-person591" type="surname" value="FORRESTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-68-person591" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18221204-68-person591" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I received him in charge with the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Mr. Drach has not sworn exactly right.</p>
               <p>
